    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "19771110_7b700392",
        "filename": "android/gps/KmlParser_unittest.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 184,
      "author": {
        "id": 1074960
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-06-02T15:23:00Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "All I found when Googling for EXPECT_FLOAT_EQ is that it \"compares up to a given precision\"--pretty vague.\nThis code seems to assume that the precision is exactly 4 fractional decimal digits.\nI think it would be better to use the full-precision expected value (as in the tests above and below).",
      "revId": "2a9f6308794794f114047673410a3b1c87b88c9f",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "f9c5ddcd_a828d322",
        "filename": "android/gps/KmlParser_unittest.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 184,
      "author": {
        "id": 1078773
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-06-02T19:42:16Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "ULPs are different from just fractional digits. If two floating point values are 1 ULP apart, there are no other possible floating point values between them. GTest allows them to be 4 ULPs apart, which is enough for practical purposes.",
      "parentUuid": "19771110_7b700392",
      "revId": "2a9f6308794794f114047673410a3b1c87b88c9f",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "f9387db2_3362b0c7",
        "filename": "android/gps/KmlParser_unittest.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 184,
      "author": {
        "id": 1074960
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-06-02T20:50:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "4 ULP seems a reasonable tolerance.\nBut how do you know that \"37.42228990140251\" and \"37.4223\" differ by less than that? \nI think the expected value should be given with the full precision. Then the 4 ULP is used only for *unavoidable* rounding errors.",
      "parentUuid": "f9c5ddcd_a828d322",
      "revId": "2a9f6308794794f114047673410a3b1c87b88c9f",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
